question: Question: In valence bond theory, this electron-pair geometry has a d-2-sp-3 hybridization. For 10 points each: [10] Name this molecular geometry. According to crystal field theory, the d-orbitals in a molecule of this geometry are split into the nonbonding triply-degenerate t-sub-2g level and the antibonding doubly-degenerate e-sub-g level.
